 but I don't think that's true.

54
00:02:50,680 --> 00:02:54,780
 I think it has boldly marched in and taken up residence.

55
00:02:54,780 --> 00:03:00,600
 We are indifferent because we've forgotten

56
00:03:00,600 --> 00:03:03,400
 what sin invites into our lives,

57
00:03:03,400 --> 00:03:06,560
 what sin invites into our homes,

58
00:03:06,560 --> 00:03:09,080
 our communities, our world.

59
00:03:09,080 --> 00:03:14,440
 Sin invites death.

60
00:03:14,440 --> 00:03:19,600
 In the story we've been looking at in this series,

61
00:03:19,600 --> 00:03:21,760
 A Different Spirit, we pick up the story

62
00:03:21,760 --> 00:03:25,600
 from Numbers 14, verses 10 to 23.

63
00:03:25,600 --> 00:03:31,080
 And all the congregation said to stone them with stones,

64
00:03:31,080 --> 00:03:32,960
 referring to Caleb and Joshua.

65
00:03:32,960 --> 00:03:35,480
 Now the glory of the Lord appeared

66
00:03:35,480 --> 00:03:37,120
 in the tabernacle of meeting

67
00:03:37,120 --> 00:03:39,800
 before all the children of Israel.

68
00:03:39,800 --> 00:03:41,560
 Then the Lord said to Moses,

69
00:03:41,560 --> 00:03:44,940
 how long will these people reject me?

70
00:03:44,940 --> 00:03:48,620
 And how long will they not believe me

71
00:03:48,620 --> 00:03:52,480
 with all the signs which I have performed among them?

72
00:03:52,480 --> 00:03:57,520
 I will strike them with the pestilence and disinherit them,

73
00:03:57,520 --> 00:03:59,880
 and I will make of you a nation greater

74
00:03:59,880 --> 00:04:01,560
 and mightier than they.

75
00:04:01,560 --> 00:04:05,320
 Moses said to the Lord,

76
00:04:05,320 --> 00:04:07,840
 then the Egyptians will hear it,

77
00:04:07,840 --> 00:04:11,280
 for by your might you brought these people up

78
00:04:11,280 --> 00:04:13,160
 from among them,

79
00:04:13,160 --> 00:04:17,340
 and they will tell it to the inhabitants of this land.

80
00:04:17,340 --> 00:04:21,160
 They have heard that you, Lord, are among this people,

81
00:04:21,160 --> 00:04:23,240
 that you, Lord, are seen face to face,

82
00:04:23,240 --> 00:04:26,160
 and your cloud stands above them.

83
00:04:26,160 --> 00:04:31,000
 And you go before them in a pillar of cloud by day

84
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:33,600
 and in a pillar of fire by night.

85
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:38,000
 Now if you kill these people as one man,

86
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:40,000
 then the nations which have heard of your fame

87
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:41,600
 will speak, saying,

88
00:04:41,600 --> 00:04:44,960
 because the Lord was not able to bring this people

89
00:04:44,960 --> 00:04:46,820
 to the land which he swore to them,

90
00:04:46,820 --> 00:04:50,600
 therefore he killed them in the wilderness.

91
00:04:50,600 --> 00:04:52,680
 And now I pray,

92
00:04:52,680 --> 00:04:55,960
 let the power of my Lord be great,

93
00:04:55,960 --> 00:04:57,920
 just as you have spoken,

94
00:04:57,920 --> 00:05:02,880
 saying the Lord is long-suffering and abundant in mercy,

95
00:05:02,880 --> 00:05:06,260
 forgiving iniquity and transgression,

96
00:05:06,260 --> 00:05:10,220
 but he by no means clears the guilty,

97
00:05:10,220 --> 00:05:13,120
 visiting the iniquity of the fathers on the children

98
00:05:13,120 --> 00:05:16,120
 to the third and fourth generation.

99
00:05:16,120 --> 00:05:20,220
 Pardon the iniquity of this people,

100
00:05:20,220 --> 00:05:24,100
 I pray according to the greatness of your mercy,

101
00:05:24,100 --> 00:05:27,880
 just as you have forgiven this people from Egypt

102
00:05:27,880 --> 00:05:29,480
 even until now.

103
00:05:29,480 --> 00:05:33,060
 Then the Lord said,

104
00:05:33,060 --> 00:05:37,040
 I have pardoned according to your word,

105
00:05:37,040 --> 00:05:39,660
 but truly as I live,

106
00:05:39,660 --> 00:05:43,260
 all the earth shall be filled with the glory of the Lord,

107
00:05:43,260 --> 00:05:46,660
 because all these men who have seen my glory

108
00:05:46,660 --> 00:05:50,700
 and the signs which I did in Egypt and in the wilderness

109
00:05:50,700 --> 00:05:55,000
 and have put me to the test now these 10 times

110
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:58,260
 and have not heeded my voice,

111
00:05:58,260 --> 00:06:01,060
 they certainly shall not see the land

112
00:06:01,060 --> 00:06:03,560
 of which I swore to their fathers,

113
00:06:03,560 --> 00:06:07,540
 nor shall any of those who rejected me see it.

114
00:06:10,100 --> 00:06:14,580
 The Israelite sin ultimately caused them to die trapped

115
00:06:14,580 --> 00:06:16,900
 and wandering in a desert.

116
00:06:16,900 --> 00:06:20,700
 It also brought death to their promises,

117
00:06:20,700 --> 00:06:23,380
 their dreams, their hopes.

118
00:06:23,380 --> 00:06:26,980
 Today many of us are wandering in a desert,

119
00:06:26,980 --> 00:06:33,080
 stuck, frustrated, experiencing lost dreams,

120
00:06:33,080 --> 00:06:37,380
 because we've invited sin into our lives.

121
00:06:37,380 --> 00:06:39,780
 We've not turned away from it,

122
00:06:39,780 --> 00:06:42,580
 but instead have made room for it.

123
00:06:42,580 --> 00:06:48,660
 We've also become indifferent to the consequences of sin.

124
00:06:48,660 --> 00:06:51,240
 We say to ourselves, God will forgive me.

125
00:06:51,240 --> 00:06:57,740
 We go back to the same sin a second, a third, a fourth,

126
00:06:57,740 --> 00:06:59,040
 a fifth time.

127
00:06:59,040 --> 00:07:02,860
 We tell ourselves, God will understand.

128
00:07:05,640 --> 00:07:09,800
 You know, the irony is, he does understand.

129
00:07:09,800 --> 00:07:15,040
 But what we often forget is that there are always

130
00:07:15,040 --> 00:07:19,560
 consequences to sin, which we bear in our bodies,

131
00:07:19,560 --> 00:07:24,560
 our minds, our homes, our communities, and our world.

132
00:07:24,560 --> 00:07:29,040
 God forgave the children of Israel,

133
00:07:29,040 --> 00:07:30,920
 but the consequences of their sin

134
00:07:30,920 --> 00:07:34,880
 was that they lost their intended future.

135
00:07:34,880 --> 00:07:37,680
 They were literally on the doorstep of it,

136
00:07:37,680 --> 00:07:39,560
 but couldn't inherit it.

137
00:07:39,560 --> 00:07:44,040
 In Numbers 13, two, God says,

138
00:07:44,040 --> 00:07:46,960
 "Send men to spy out the land of Canaan,

139
00:07:46,960 --> 00:07:51,300
 "which I am giving to the children of Israel."

140
00:07:51,300 --> 00:07:55,960
 He says, "Which I am giving,"

141
00:07:55,960 --> 00:07:58,920
 not that I'm thinking about giving.

142
00:07:58,920 --> 00:08:04,380
 He said that I am giving.

143
00:08:05,380 --> 00:08:08,380
 You know, when God first asked Moses

144
00:08:08,380 --> 00:08:10,660
 to liberate the nation of Israel

145
00:08:10,660 --> 00:08:13,660
 from the oppression of slavery in Egypt,

146
00:08:13,660 --> 00:08:17,180
 God, Moses asked God,

147
00:08:17,180 --> 00:08:21,300
 "What is your name?"

148
00:08:21,300 --> 00:08:24,840
 He said to God, "Suppose I go to the Israelites

149
00:08:24,840 --> 00:08:26,800
 "and say to them, the God of your fathers

150
00:08:26,800 --> 00:08:30,200
 "has sent me to you, and they ask me, what is your name?

151
00:08:30,200 --> 00:08:32,880
 "Then what shall I tell them?"

152
00:08:33,720 --> 00:08:37,960
 God says to Moses, "Ihir asher ihir,"

153
00:08:37,960 --> 00:08:40,960
 I am who I am.

154
00:08:40,960 --> 00:08:43,120
 This is what you are to say to the Israelites,

155
00:08:43,120 --> 00:08:46,000
 I am has sent me to you.

156
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:50,520
 The Hebrew alphabet gives a clue to the meaning.

157
00:08:50,520 --> 00:08:52,920
 This name begins with the first letter

158
00:08:52,920 --> 00:08:55,320
 of the Hebrew alphabet, Aleph,

159
00:08:55,320 --> 00:08:57,960
 which speaks of the future tense.

160
00:08:57,960 --> 00:09:00,880
 Therefore, this name can be translated,

161
00:09:00,880 --> 00:09:03,300
 I will be who I will be.

162
00:09:03,300 --> 00:09:07,700
 God is saying he's not only with us right now,

163
00:09:07,700 --> 00:09:10,800
 but he goes ahead of us into our future,

164
00:09:10,800 --> 00:09:13,560
 which may be unknown to us,

165
00:09:13,560 --> 00:09:16,660
 but is completely known to God.

166
00:09:16,660 --> 00:09:20,680
 God is saying, I will be whatever I choose to be

167
00:09:20,680 --> 00:09:23,280
 in the circumstances you face in life,

168
00:09:23,280 --> 00:09:27,640
 your healer, your deliverer, your provider, your protector,

169
00:09:27,640 --> 00:09:30,080
 I will be that for you.

170
00:09:30,080 --> 00:09:33,600
 When God said, I am giving this land

171
00:09:33,600 --> 00:09:35,200
 to the children of Israel,

172
00:09:35,200 --> 00:09:38,720
 he was backing up his promise with his name,

173
00:09:38,720 --> 00:09:44,120
 with the essence of who he was, with his character.

174
00:09:44,120 --> 00:09:47,040
 This is significant.

175
00:09:47,040 --> 00:09:50,920
 Let's look at what happens when the spies return

176
00:09:50,920 --> 00:09:53,380
 from spying out the promised land.

177
00:09:53,380 --> 00:09:56,940
 They share, we went to the land where you sent us,

178
00:09:56,940 --> 00:10:00,420
 it truly flows with milk and honey.

179
00:10:00,420 --> 00:10:03,940
 But the people who dwell in the land are strong,

180
00:10:03,940 --> 00:10:08,220
 the cities are fortified, and there's giants.

181
00:10:08,220 --> 00:10:11,020
 We are not able to go up against the people,

182
00:10:11,020 --> 00:10:13,620
 they are stronger than us.

183
00:10:13,620 --> 00:10:16,980
 These spies give the children of Israel

184
00:10:16,980 --> 00:10:18,460
 a bad report of the land,

185
00:10:18,460 --> 00:10:22,100
 saying that the land devours its inhabitants,

186
00:10:22,100 --> 00:10:25,300
 and we were like grasshoppers.

187
00:10:26,220 --> 00:10:29,420
 What just happened here?

188
00:10:29,420 --> 00:10:33,580
 God said, I am giving this land to you.

189
00:10:33,580 --> 00:10:39,500
 The 10 spies say, we are not able, they are stronger.

190
00:10:39,500 --> 00:10:43,220
 These men were denying the word of God,

191
00:10:43,220 --> 00:10:47,380
 the promises of God, they were denying God himself,

192
00:10:47,380 --> 00:10:50,180
 his strength and his power.

193
00:10:50,180 --> 00:10:52,900
 They were saying, these people are stronger than us

194
00:10:52,900 --> 00:10:54,820
 and our God.

195
00:10:54,820 --> 00:10:57,380
 God is not able to give us this land.

196
00:10:57,380 --> 00:11:02,300
 They lost sight of their own identity

197
00:11:02,300 --> 00:11:03,980
 as the children of God,

198
00:11:03,980 --> 00:11:08,420
 and they lost sight of God's identity.

199
00:11:08,420 --> 00:11:09,900
 I am.

200
00:11:09,900 --> 00:11:14,600
 They not only lost sight of it, they denied it.

201
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:16,940
 They sinned by not trusting God's vision

202
00:11:16,940 --> 00:11:19,340
 and rebelling against it.

203
00:11:19,340 --> 00:11:22,160
 When Caleb and Joshua tried to remind them

204
00:11:22,160 --> 00:11:25,400
 of who they are and who God is,

205
00:11:25,400 --> 00:11:28,260
 the Israelites don't even want to listen.

206
00:11:28,260 --> 00:11:32,480
 Numbers 14, 10 to 11.

207
00:11:32,480 --> 00:11:36,720
 And all the congregation said to stone them.

208
00:11:36,720 --> 00:11:39,620
 Now the glory of the Lord appeared

209
00:11:39,620 --> 00:11:41,540
 in the tabernacle of meeting

210
00:11:41,540 --> 00:11:44,260
 before all the children of Israel.

211
00:11:44,260 --> 00:11:45,880
 Then the Lord said to Moses,

212
00:11:45,880 --> 00:11:48,980
 how long will these people reject me?

213
00:11:48,980 --> 00:11:51,560
 How long will they not believe me

214
00:11:51,560 --> 00:11:55,480
 with all the signs which I've performed among them?

215
00:11:55,480 --> 00:12:00,220
 Furthermore, the 10 spies sin

216
00:12:00,220 --> 00:12:03,520
 because they sway the whole community

217
00:12:03,520 --> 00:12:05,880
 to reject God's words.

218
00:12:05,880 --> 00:12:09,620
 They sway them to lose sight of the grapes

219
00:12:09,620 --> 00:12:12,380
 and only see the giants.

220
00:12:12,380 --> 00:12:17,540
 How much sin enters our lives

221
00:12:17,540 --> 00:12:20,900
 because we lose sight of our identity and God?

222
00:12:21,800 --> 00:12:26,800
 And distrust God's words and deny his very character.

223
00:12:26,800 --> 00:12:32,100
 The other day I was going to catch the E41,

224
00:12:32,100 --> 00:12:35,120
 which is the bus I take every morning to get to my school.

225
00:12:35,120 --> 00:12:38,460
 And if somebody had said to me that morning,

226
00:12:38,460 --> 00:12:40,600
 look, when you get to your bus line,

227
00:12:40,600 --> 00:12:43,360
 you're going to be second or third in line.

228
00:12:43,360 --> 00:12:45,020
 I would have said, great.

229
00:12:45,020 --> 00:12:47,560
 Because actually it doesn't matter

230
00:12:47,560 --> 00:12:49,480
 where you are in the bus line,

231
00:12:49,480 --> 00:12:52,100
 you always get a seat on that bus.

232
00:12:52,100 --> 00:12:56,320
 It's never full, there's always empty seats left over.

233
00:12:56,320 --> 00:13:01,200
 So as I approached the bus line that morning,

234
00:13:01,200 --> 00:13:04,480
 I noticed that there was one man lined up.

235
00:13:04,480 --> 00:13:08,660
 I was about five metres away from him,

236
00:13:08,660 --> 00:13:11,640
 walking down the street towards him.

237
00:13:11,640 --> 00:13:14,200
 At the same time, I noticed that across the road

238
00:13:14,200 --> 00:13:16,040
 on the other side of the road,

239
00:13:16,040 --> 00:13:19,300
 there was a woman who was heading to the bus line as well.

240
00:13:19,300 --> 00:13:21,560
 I recognised her as a regular traveller.

241
00:13:21,560 --> 00:13:23,240
 She was there every morning.

242
00:13:23,240 --> 00:13:27,140
 She was about 15 metres away from the bus line.

243
00:13:27,140 --> 00:13:30,600
 Now, if we continued as we were,

244
00:13:30,600 --> 00:13:32,960
 I would have ended up second in the bus line

245
00:13:32,960 --> 00:13:35,760
 and she would have ended up third in the bus line.

246
00:13:35,760 --> 00:13:37,900
 All good, right?

247
00:13:37,900 --> 00:13:40,400
 Apparently not.

248
00:13:40,400 --> 00:13:45,560
 As she caught my eye, she began to run.

249
00:13:48,140 --> 00:13:50,000
 Now, she wasn't running to catch the bus,

250
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:51,320
 it hadn't come yet.

251
00:13:51,320 --> 00:13:55,720
 She was running to be second in line.

252
00:13:55,720 --> 00:14:00,000
 Now, remember I said that if someone had told me

253
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:02,640
 that morning that I would be second or third in line,

254
00:14:02,640 --> 00:14:04,920
 I would have said, "Great."

255
00:14:04,920 --> 00:14:06,900
 But all of a sudden it mattered.

256
00:14:06,900 --> 00:14:13,000
 These were the strange thoughts that ran through my head.

257
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:15,660
 She's trying to take second place from me.

258
00:14:16,540 --> 00:14:18,120
 Can't she see me?

259
00:14:18,120 --> 00:14:19,600
 I'm right here.

260
00:14:19,600 --> 00:14:23,000
 Oh my goodness, she's running.

261
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:27,180
 And then I thought, "Oh no you don't.

262
00:14:27,180 --> 00:14:30,180
 Not on my watch."

263
00:14:30,180 --> 00:14:33,980
 Now, thankfully I didn't break into a run.

264
00:14:33,980 --> 00:14:35,960
 I didn't want to be that obvious,

265
00:14:35,960 --> 00:14:39,000
